far east suite to a high bright use of a metal hat mute in 
happygolucky local 
alto saxophonist norris turneys romantic isfahan with the 
other instruments orchestrated to swirl around him was another of 
many special movements in the exotically beautiful far east 
suite 
act 2 started with the six train songs from choo choo of 
1924 when ellington was 25 to loco madi written at the 
university of wisconsin in madison in 1972 
david berger who transcribed the evenings music from 
recordings by the ellington band conducted for him day break 
express from 1933 is the most dazzling of all ellingtons train 
pieces he said it comes out of the night into the morning at 
100 miles an hour the band which was wonderfully rehearsed 
fresh fullbodied but never heavy rushed day break express 
past all depots 
that was followed by happygolucky local from 1946 from 
which jimmy forrest appropriated the main melody for night 
train 
