the new government of president alberto 
fujimori has announced a harsh austerity plan aimed at ending 
hyperinflation and rebuilding a collapsed economy troops were 
deployed to head off any food riots 
subsidy cuts and a lifting of price controls mean peruvians will 
pay a lot more for food gasoline and basic services economy and 
prime minister juan hurtado miller said in a nationally televised 
speech wednesday night 
hurtado said a gallon of gasoline would cost 30 times more 
today the price of milk and bread were to triple while noodles 
were to cost five times what they did wednesday he said 
this is the price we must pay said hurtado this is the 
period for cleaning up and detoxifying 
the tough policy is a switch from the campaign platform of 
gradual reform that helped catapult fujimori from a virtual unknown 
at the beginning of the year to the victor in the june election 
his opponent acclaimed novelist mario vargas llosa had backed 
speedy marketoriented reform 
but fujimori who took office july 28 has been told by 
international creditors that he must control inflation before 
theyll lend him more money 
soldiers and police took up positions throughout the capital 
before hurtados speech on tuesday the government declared a 
state of emergency in lima and 10 large cities fearing food riots 
would break out after the austerity measures were announced 
mobs on tuesday looted the central markets of both lima and the 
nearby port of callao before being controlled by police and 
soldiers 
bread noodles beans sugar cooking oil and milk have all 
disappeared from store shelves in recent days this was due to both 
panicbuying by consumers and hoarding by merchants who were 
awaiting higher prices 
most stores and market stalls remained closed in the hours 
before hurtado spoke 
in his speech hurtado vowed to cut inflation to less than the 
latin american average by the end of the year he said the 
government will increase its income and spend only what it earns 
all price controls and subsidies will end he said 
the austerity measures also include emergency taxes on the 
wealthy and a restructuring of import duties hurtado said 
press reports have said the government plans to devalue perus 
inti by at least 50 percent though hurtado made no mention of such 
a move wednesday 
to soften the effects of the measures on perus millions of poor 
people the government will set up soup kitchens and directly 
subsidize water and bus services hurtado said 
fujimori has said that harsh measures are needed to stop perus 
fall into economic chaos annual inflation tops 3000 percent four 
of five people lack steady work and the economy has shrunk 20 
percent in two years 
fujimori has taken office with peru in the midst of its worst 
drought this century with up to 70 percent of the yearly 
production of many basic crops destroyed he must also deal with a 
worsening guerrilla war that in the past 10 years has claimed 
20000 victims 
tension in the capital increased in the days leading up to 
hurtado millers announcement 
the dollar doubled in value in the first three days of the week 
with its price jumping from 200000 intis to 400000 
many stores doubled their prices even before hurtado spoke 
wednesday getting a jump on the expected end of price controls 
other stores remained closed for fear that looting would break 
out most market stalls were shuttered and those were open 
displayed vastly reduced stocks 
drivers formed lines dozens of cars long to fill up before 
gasoline prices jumped 
