allowing the united states to use the strategic nato air base at 
incirlik for any military intervention in the persian gulf 
britain said it would send two squadrons of warplanes and a 
number of groundtoair missiles and to defend saudi arabia and 
other gulf states defense secretary tom king said today the 
defense ministry said each squadron consisted of about 12 planes 
king said britains contribution to the multinational effort 
also included three mine sweepers to be deployed initially to the 
eastern mediterranean the british destroyer hms york is already in 
the gulf and two frigates are expected to arrive there this 
weekend 
britain decided wednesday to join the multinational force 
following a formal request for british assistance from king fahd of 
saudi arabia 
france one of the few members of the 16nation nato alliance 
with an appropriate military capability said wednesday that it had 
not been asked by saudi arabia to send forces 
france which has two ships just outside the persian gulf and a 
frigate with exocet missiles en route said french participation 
was not envisaged at this stage in a multinational force 
president hosni mubarak of egypt said wednesday that his country 
had not sent troops but advocatged an arab multinational force 
iraqi president saddam hussein whose forces invaded neighboring 
kuwait one week ago to touch off the crisis has denied he intends 
to invade saudi arabia but iraqi forces are reported massing on 
the borders with saudi arabia and turkey 
the portuguese foreign minister said late wednesday that 
portugal has granted the united states use of the air base at lajes 
in the azores islands in the midatlantic in the buildup operation 
of us forces in saudi arabia that began wednesday 
portuguese news reports said six us air force midair refueling 
planes landed at the lajes base on wednesday the base is shared by 
portuguese and us forces 
italy has agreed to let bases be used to help facilitate 
transport of troops and equipment and for logistical support prime 
minister giulio andreottis office announced wednesday 
spain whose prime minister felipe gonzalez opposes outside 
intervention in the persian gulf nonetheless agreed wednesday to 
allow the united states to use four jointly operated military bases 
to support us troops 
bonn signaled readiness wednesday to allow the us military to 
use american facilities in west germany as a basis for 
operations for soldiers headed to saudi arabia 
west germany said tuesday its constitution bars use of german 
troops outside the country 
greece said wednesday that nine us support planes were granted 
permission to pass through greek airspace on their way to the 
persian gulf 
