invaded kuwait last week the security council unanimously 
condemned iraq and demanded that it withdraw 
yemen abstained from both earlier resolutions cuba abstained 
from the call for an economic boycott 
the council includes the five permanent members the united 
states britain china france and the soviet union and 10 other 
members canada colombia cuba ethiopia finland ivory coast 
malaysia romania yemen and zaire 
the security council handles issues relating to international 
peace and security its resolutions are legally binding on all un 
members although past council resolutions have often been ignored 
or flouted 
the united nations has no enforcement mechanism 
