king fahd in his first address to 
the nation since the iraqi invasion of kuwait said thursday his 
decision to seek foreign military help was a defensive move forced 
by the iraqi aggression 
it was the first time the saudi government had explained to its 
people the arrival of tens of thousands of american troops 
fahd called the takeover of neighboring kuwait the most 
horrible aggression the arab nation has known in its modern 
history and said his request for foreign military help was aimed 
at restoring peace to the region 
fahd demanded that in addition to an iraqi troop pullout the 
alsabah royal family return to power in kuwait 
following the invasion of kuwait on aug 2 the iraqis massed 
large numbers of troops on the border of the kingdom fahd said 
faced with this bitter reality and out of keenness to 
safeguard its territory and economy the kingdom expressed a 
desire to arab and friendly forces to participate in the defense 
task he said 
the king spoke as us airborne rapid deployment forces and 
fighter jets poured into saudi arabia 
an official statement later distributed by the saudi press 
agency said the troop buildup was to be completed friday 
it expressed the kingdoms deep appreciation to all states 
that were sending troops their involvement reflected keenness to 
see security and stability prevail in the arabian gulf region until 
normal conditions are restored as well as the legitimate authority 
in the sister state of kuwait and all consequences of the iraqi 
invasion are eliminated 
diplomatic sources noted this would coincide with the emergency 
arab summit being held in cairo the summit was expected to take up 
egyptian president hosni mubaraks proposal to line up a panarab 
force which would replace the iraqi occupation troops inside 
kuwait until the differences over land oil and money that sparked 
the invasion could be settled 
referring to the foreign troops in saudi territory the king 
said these forces from friendly powers are here temporarily 
they are to help defend the kingdom participate in joint 
exercises and will leave here as soon as the kingdom so demands 
he said 
fahd stressed that inviting western and arab forces to the 
kingdom was not directed against anyone but a purely defensive 
measure 
the landing of the thousands of foreign troops has been cloaked 
from ordinary saudis since they were being deployed at the 
northeastern desert edge of the kingdom 
the area is known as hafr albaten where one of the worlds 
biggest military cities was completed in 1985 the city can 
accommodate up to 70000 officers and soldiers aside from 
dependents 
a 10000strong fledgling rapid deployment force from saudi 
arabia kuwait and the other four partners in the gulf copperation 
council alliance bahrain oman qatar and the united arab 
emirates is also based at hafr albaten 
we feel them but we dont see them said a resident reached 
by telephone in the vital oil center of the eastern province where 
the troops were headed 
aside from a run on newspapers and portable radios residents 
went about their lives remaining mainly indoors as usual as the 
summer temperatures soared to about 100 degrees 
there has been no panic or mass evacuation of the estimated 45 
million foreign workers and their dependents in the kingdom but 
some foreigners especially dependents were leaving if their stay 
was not necessary 
many workers from the indian subcontinent were lined up seeking 
visas 
