briefing reporters on bakers meetings said that in the event 
there were to be fullscale hostilities i am quite confident that 
we could count upon our allies the turks 
the official who demanded anonymity added weve long had 
cooperative military relationships with turkey i think the turks 
see the threat that president saddam hussein represents and i 
think they see the threat his longrange missile capability and his 
chemical weapons capability presents to many many nations 
describing turkey as exposed to a potential iraqi attack 
the official said i think they know that the allies are going to 
be there and that the united states is going to be there and they 
are going to be there for the united states 
on the other hand baker said turkey had not committed itself to 
join the multinational force the united states is organizing to 
enforce the economic sanctions approved by the un security 
council 
turkey has not and thats a question that the turkish 
government will have to consider baker said 
the strategy of the bush administration is to encircle iraq with 
a diverse group of nations including turkey a staunch us ally 
in nato and two bitter adversaries syria and iran 
baker was cheered by the unanimous un security council vote 
condemning iraqs annexation of kuwait 
our strategy from the very beginning is to try to bring about 
as much of an international consensus in condemnation of this 
action and support of an immediate withdrawal as we could an 
administration official said 
asked if he would like saddam hussein to look at a map and see 
all those countries lining up against him the official broke into 
a grin 
yeah you bet he said 
