everybody seems to be hoping that this production will be 
coming on real fast but what if theres a hitch and a cold 
winter he said the system already is going to be stretched 
everywhere 
meanwhile the international energy agency meeting in paris 
took the first step thursday to what could result in a draw down of 
government stockpiles in europe the united states and japan to 
help fill temporary shortages 
although the agency traditionally has looked upon a 7 percent 
drop in supplies as the trigger point for scheduling a 
coordinated draw down the government energy officials stopped 
short of ordering one thursday doing it in response to the 9 
percent supply loss represented by kuwait and iraq 
instead they agreed to begin collecting daily statistics on 
