<TEXT>
frank lorenzo announced thursday he would sell 
his stake in continental airline holdings inc ending a stormy 
tenure at the helm of what was once the nations largest airline 
company 
here is a rundown of highlights in his career 
1963 hired by trans world airlines as a financial analyst 
his first professional job 
1965 becomes manager of the financial analysis department at 
eastern airlines 
1966 forms an airline consulting firm with harvard business 
school classmate robert carney to explore business opportunities 
1972 becomes president of texas international airlines after 
a holding company he forms injects new capital into the ailing 
airline 
197377 rejuvenates texas international using discounted 
peanut fares more efficient routes and upgraded fleet 
1980 forms new york air to compete with eastern shuttle 
service between new york and washington 
1981 wins control of continental airlines over a rival 
managementled buyout bid 
1982 merges texas international and continental under texas 
air corp 
1983 lays off 15 percent of work force to bring down labor 
costs hires permanent replacements for striking machinists files 
for bankruptcy protection to reorganize voiding labor contracts 
offers to rehire employees at half pay 
1985 loses a bid for trans world airlines to financier carl 
icahn and a bid for frontier airlines to people express 
1986 acquires eastern airlines and people express to form the 
nations biggest airline company 
1987 introduces discount maxsaver fares and announces plans 
to cut labor costs 
1988 undertakes a joint marketing operation with scandinavian 
airlines system a leading european carrier 
1989 rejects eastern union demands in contract negotiations 
workers strike in march lorenzo puts the carrier under federal 
bankruptcy protection and begins to sell many of easterns 
important assets including the northeast shuttle parent company 
loses 8856 million for the year an industry record 
januaryfebruary 1990 drastically reduces proposal for 
repaying eastern creditors and faces increased problems in 
bankruptcy court 
april 1990 loses control of eastern to a courtappointed 
trustee martin shugrue renames texas air to continental airlines 
holdings inc 
aug 9 1990 announces resignation as chairman and chief 
executive officer 
