<TEXT>
thousands of american combat troops took up 
defensive positions thursday in the heart of saudi arabias vital 
oilproducing province as us military strategists prepared to 
fight a high intensity war on a vast scale 
the bush administration kept its official silence on details of 
the us troop deployment codenamed desert shield president 
bush ordered the operation monday saying he hoped to deter iraqi 
president saddam hussein from sending his millionman army into the 
kingdom the worlds largest oil exporter 
at least 2300 american ground troops landed in saudi arabia on 
the first day of the deployments wednesday and pete williams the 
chief pentagon spokesman said theres much more to come over 
the next several days and possibly weeks 
this is an operation that is going to continue for several 
days one might say many days williams told reporters 
as the buildup of iraqi forces in occupied kuwait swelled 
pentagon and administration sources revealed that military leaders 
have prepared longrange plans that could put 200000 to 250000 
us troops on saudi soil 
we have contingency plans that could result in the insertion 
of up to 200000 to 250000 ground forces before its all done 
said a pentagon source who spoke on condition of anonymity the 
united states is prepared to put many divisions on the ground 
the sources said the plan would be evaluated at each step and 
such a large force might never be necessary 
husseins response will determine exactly how much combat 
power we put on the ground the source said the idea of 
deterrence is to place your forces so that they never have to be 
used 
if deterrence fails and we fight it will be a highintensity 
war with many casualties many chemical casualties much equipment 
destroyed the oficial said it will mean warfare on a scale 
that we havent seen since world war ii 
a force of 250000 ground troops would account for a significant 
fraction of the fighting power of the 940000 activeduty troops in 
the army and the amrine corps it would also require thousands more 
in warships and airplanes in the theater of operations and in the 
supply train stretching back to the united states 
williams said us intelligence reports from the middle east 
indicated that saddam was sending additional troops into kuwait 
the tiny but oilrich country his forces seized a week ago 
prompting international sanctions and the us military response 
williams added however that there were no signs of offensive 
operations by the iraqis who numbered about 120000 in kuwait 
in a lateafternoon update the pentagon said if all iraqi 
combat units that were moving south in iraq went as far as kuwait 
they would increase the number of troops there to about 170000 
the statement said there seems to be some gathering of iraqi 
troops on the turkish border but no significant gathering is 
noted on the jordanian border 
the iraqi troops in kuwait seem to be in a defensive 
posture he said theyre holding on to what theyve 
acquired williams also said he could not confirm reports that 
iraq had readied chemical weapons in the border area 
the us forces though greatly outnumbered by a battlehardened 
iraqi army have sophisticated air and naval weapons designed to 
shatter advancing armored columns that would have to cross desert 
wastelands to reach saudi oil fields 
diplomatic sources in the middle east said elements of the us 
82nd airborne division after arriving wednesday at the saudi air 
base at dhahran along the persian gulf coastline headed for a 
remote military installation near the iraqi border 
williams said american troops were spending thursday unloading 
their equipment preparing their defensive positions and planning 
unspecified joint maneuvers with saudi soldiers 
in addition to a nineship us navy armada plying the persian 
gulf two american aircraft carrier battle groups were stationed 
nearby the uss independence with six accompanying combatant and 
supply ships was patrolling the arabian sea at the mouth of the 
gulf and the uss eisenhower with three combatant and two supply 
ships was in the red sea near the end of a saudi pipeline that 
carries iraqi crude not counting supply ships at least 21 surface 
warships were in the area or headed toward it 
williams said the three warships accompanying the eisenhower 
included one that was added on thursday he also said the uss 
saratoga aircraft carrier battle group including nine vessels was 
headed for the mediterranean sea 
the pentagon spokesman said five us airborne warning and 
control system aircraft were in place in saudi arabia as well as 
an unspecified number of f15 fighter jets from langley air force 
base va the f15 contingent was believed to include two 
squadrons or about 46 aircraft 
the middle east diplomatic sources speaking only on condition 
of anonymity said at least portions of the american ground force 
were settling in at the remote military installation at hafr 
albaten just south of the iraqi border the base is in the 
alhajarah region a stony plain traversed by the transarabian 
pipe line which extends 1068 miles from the gulf coast to 
southern lebanon 
the main landing for american aircraft is the dhahran airfield 
near the vital oil terminal at ras tanura the main saudi oil 
producing area is part of an irregular plain ending in a ragged 
coastline of tidal flats sand spits and offshore sandbars 
extending over this plain and along the gulf coast are most of 
the major oil facilities that process and export oil that is vital 
to the global economy saudi arabia is the worlds thirdlargest 
oil producer behind the soviet union and the united states because 
of its small domestic oil needs its export volume of about 5 
million barrels a day is the largest in the world 
saudi arabia provides about 15 percent of american oil imports 
making it the largest single foreign supplier 
