all have been in office for eight years or more and face their most 
serious challenges yet 
nearly all the new england governors have suffered along with 
the regions economy and the three democrats michael dukakis in 
massachusetts william oneill in connecticut and madeleine kunin 
in vermont all decided not to run again 
meanwhile republican govs john mckernan of maine and edward 
diprete of rhode island are trailing their democratic challengers 
in the polls 
dipretes troubles stem not only from rhode islands flagging 
