an administrative law judge ruled in favor of the securities and 
exchange commission against william h mathis barring the account 
executive with bear stearns amp co in atlanta ga from any 
dealings with secregistered brokerages for at least two years 
mathis a former national football league running back who 
captained the new york jets team that won the 1969 super bowl can 
reapply for sec approval to return to the business after two years 
as long as it is in a nonsupervisory position administrative law 
judge brenda p murray said in a 27page decision 
