<TEXT>
emergency oil stockpiles do not yet need to be 
tapped to make up for an embargo against iraq and kuwait delegates 
from industrialized nations decided thursday 
but the 21nation international energy agency will take steps to 
sharpen preparedness if the situation deteriorates said 
chairman ulrich engelmann we must be prepared for that 
concluding a daylong meeting to assess the impact of the 
boycott the iea decided enough oil exists on world markets to 
forestall dipping into emergency reserves 
engelmann blamed speculation for dramatic increases in oil 
prices but said the higher prices should dampen demand he 
predicted some opec members will boost production but did not say 
which ones or by how much 
conservation and switches from oilbased fuels to natural gas 
would also help to keep stocks high he said 
the iea is empowered to help its members survive the potentially 
damaging loss of loss of 42 million barrels of oil per day 
produced by iraq and kuwait 
the members are ready to use their emergency stockpiles and to 
share them with each other if necessary said a canadian delegate 
on condition of anonymity 
iea members include the united states canada japan australia 
new zealand and most western european countries except france 
finland and iceland 
oil supplies have not been affected by the boycott yet 
engelmann said because shipments from iraq or kuwait to iea 
countries normally take 10 days the united nations imposed the 
embargo monday to punish iraqs invasion of its smaller neighbor a 
week ago 
delegates will meet again in two weeks when the market could 
begin to feel the shortfall 
the ieas two main weapons are to inject emergency stockpiles 
into the market or share oil with members suffering the worst 
shortages 
the emergency stocksharing program is the groups ultimate 
weapon it is supposed to take effect when 7 percent of projected 
supplies to the entire iea or any of its members is obstructed 
once triggered the system allots oil reserves to member 
countries according to a preset formula 
us assistant energy secretary john easton said neither measure 
is immediately necessary but the united states favors putting oil 
from its 590 millionbarrel stockpile on the market as simpler 
we will draw down the strategic petroleum reserve in 
cooperation with our allies if the severity of the situation 
warrants it he said 
the iea issued a communique urging countries to refrain from 
abnormal purchases of petroleum 
companies should show restraint by avoiding abnormal spot 
market purchases or other undesirable purchases of oil during the 
period of this supply disruption the statement said 
engelmann of west germany said the group found no evidence oil 
companies had taken advantage of the invasion to boost prices 
iea executive director helga steeg said the group does not plan 
to deal with the organization of petroleum exporting countries on 
supply questions iran has shown interest in such talks 
opec president sadek boussena said in algeria on wednesday that 
individual opec members should avoid breaking ranks to increase 
production unilaterally 
</TEXT>
