bonds the investment company institute said thursday 
the rise to a new high of 40194 billion in the sevenday 
period ended wednesday followed a revised 130 billion increase 
in the funds assets the previous week according to the 
washingtonbased mutual fund trade group 
the previous weeks total also was revised to 39591 billion 
the influx of cash came as iraqs invasion of kuwait and 
subsequent tensions caused gyrations in the stock and bond markets 
due to speculation about the possible economic impact of events in 
the key oilproducing region 
investors moved out of stocks and bonds in light of unsettled 
markets and placed their money in money market funds said jacob 
dreyer vice president and chief economist at the institute 
the biggest weekly rise in the funds assets 964 billion in 
the week ended oct 21 1987 came during the stock market 
collapse as investors sought safe havens for their money 
