<TEXT>
william h donaldson a wall street veteran and 
friend of president bush was named thursday as chairman and chief 
executive of the new york stock exchange 
donaldson 59 will succeed john j phelan jr who won wide 
praise for safely steering the nations largest exchange through 
the 1987 stock market crash and helping to avert a protracted world 
financial crisis 
the nyses board also named president richard a grasso who had 
wanted the top post as executive vice chairman with expanded 
responsibilities both appointments take effect jan 1 
donaldson a cofounder of the investment firm donaldson lufkin 
amp jenrette inc brings broad experience on wall street in 
government and academia to one of the most highprofile jobs in 
american business 
he arrives at a time of rapid technological change global 
market interdependence and increased competition overseas that 
threaten to redefine the basic structure of the 198yearold 
exchange a worldwide symbol of capitalism 
this is one of the most challenging jobs in the country 
today donaldson told a news conference at the exchange in lower 
manhattan the opportunity to be here at a time of great change 
appeals to my spirit 
donaldsons first job on wall street was at the old brokerage 
gh walker amp co run by bushs uncle herbert walker donaldson 
was a classmate of the presidents brother jonathan at yale 
university and is friends with the bush family 
in 1959 just one year out of harvard business school donaldson 
and two friends founded donaldson lufkin amp jenrette he left in 
1973 after the company grew from its initial 100000 investment to 
the nations 10th largest brokerage 
donaldson served in the nixon and ford administrations first as 
an undersecretary of state to henry kissinger in 197374 before 
becoming special white house counsel to vice president nelson 
rockefeller 
a yale trustee donaldson in 1975 helped create a graduate 
business school and served as dean of yales school of organization 
and management until 1980 when he returned to wall street to open 
a private investment firm donaldson enterprises inc 
hes coming from a major background said muriel siebert a 
wall street veteran who heads her own brokerage he knows the 
nyse from a business basis because he has headed a firm he knows 
his way around washington and politics 
the combination is important said primerica inc president 
jeffrey lane a board member of the competing american stock 
exchange the industry needs a strong leader who can pick up the 
baton that john phelan is passing he has all the right 
credentials 
donaldson becomes the fourth fulltime paid chairman of the big 
board since the job was created in 1972 he was tabbed by a 
ninemember search panel appointed after phelan in february 
announced plans to retire at the end of the year 
donaldson is known on wall street for leading and winning a 
fight against the nyse to lift a ban on publicly owned securities 
firms after the exchange agreed to let dlj sell stock to the 
public in 1969 many securities firms followed 
donaldson said among his main concerns will be the nyses role 
in global securities trading and the maintenance restoration and 
enhancement of public confidence in the operation of the market 
that eroded after the 1987 crash 
among other challenges he cited new forms of electronic 
trading the prospect of roundtheclock securities trading 
monitoring new regulation and wild fluctuations that have shaken 
public confidence in the stock market 
donaldson praised phelans administration for being responsive 
to the unexpected during such events as the market gyrations 
that followed iraqs invasion of kuwait last week 
phelan chairman since may 1984 will remain an advisor for nyse 
relations with foreign stock exchanges he currently is chairman of 
the international federation of stock exchanges and has traveled 
extensively during his tenure cultivating ties with markets abroad 
phelan 59 said he will serve as chairman of the aspen 
institute a policy think tank that arranges speakers on various 
issues continue his work on foreign markets at the exchange and 
serve on corporate boards 
richard c breeden chairman of the securities and exchange 
commission said the sec looked forward to working with donaldson 
he said phelan consistently demonstrated strength wisdom and 
vision and helped to maintain both the integrity and the 
competitiveness of the us securities markets 
grasso 44 is a 22year nyse veteran his additional 
responsibilities were described by people familiar with the 
selections as an inducement to keep him at the exchange it was 
widely known he had wanted the chairmans job 
</TEXT>
