grain analysts predicted a rally in corn and soybean futures 
prices after the agriculture department on thursday released 
harvest projections that fell short of market expectations 
soybean futures rose thursday on the chicago board of trade in 
anticipation of the report wheat futures also advanced while corn 
retreated 
on other commodity markets gold and silver futures advanced 
oil futures fell and livestock and meat futures were mostly lower 
