stocks to 121 billion bushels from last months 113 billion the 
increase reflects expectations for a 19 million metric ton increase 
in soviet union grain production over last year and a corresponding 
8 million ton drop in soviet grain imports 
the corn market will have to grapple with what the wheat 
market has been grappling with less export demand karlin said 
he said that in light of the projected decline in soviet grain 
purchases and the markets recent weakness im not so sure 
whether the positive implication will be able to hold over long 
term 
